1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,610
Big success calls for persons who continually set higher standards for themselves and others,

2
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:12,850
persons who are searching for ways to increase efficiency, to get more output at lower cost,

3
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:14,850
do more with less effort.

4
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:20,290
Top success is reserved for the I-can-do-it-better kind of person.

5
00:00:20,880 --> 00:00:26,449
General Electric uses the slogan, Progress is our most important product.

6
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:30,530
Why not make progress your most important product?

7
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:34,370
The I-can-do-better philosophy works magic.

8
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:37,409
When you ask yourself, how can I do better?

9
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:43,489
Your creative power is switched on and ways for doing things better suggest themselves.

10
00:00:44,159 --> 00:00:51,650
Here is a daily exercise that will help you discover and develop the power of the I-can-do-better attitude.

11
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:59,409
Each day, before you begin work, devote 10 minutes to thinking, how can I do a better job today?

12
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:03,810
Ask, what can I do today to encourage my employees?

13
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:07,090
What special favor can I do for my customers?

14
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:10,449
How can I increase my personal efficiency?

15
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:13,570
This exercise is simple, but it works.

16
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:19,090
Try it, and you'll find unlimited creative ways to win greater success.

17
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:25,969
Just about every time my wife and I would get together with a certain couple,

18
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:29,250
the conversation would turn to working wives.

19
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:35,330
Mrs. S had worked several years before her marriage, and she had genuinely liked it.

20
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:42,050
But now, she'd say, I've got two youngsters in school, a home to manage, and meals to prepare.

21
00:01:42,159 --> 00:01:44,209
I simply haven't got time.

22
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:51,010
Then one Sunday evening, Mr. and Mrs. S and their children were in an automobile accident.

23
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:59,650
Mrs. S and the youngsters escaped serious injury, but Mr. S received a back injury that left him permanently disabled.

24
00:01:59,919 --> 00:02:03,570
Now Mrs. S had no choice but to go to work.

25
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:12,610
When we saw her several months after the accident, we were amazed to find how well she had adjusted to her new responsibilities.

26
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:20,370
You know, she said, six months ago I never dreamed I could possibly manage the house and work full time.

27
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:25,489
But after the accident, I just made up my mind that I had to find the time.

28
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:29,570
Believe me, my efficiency has gone up 100%.

29
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:33,969
I discovered a lot of things I was doing didn't need to be done at all.

30
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:38,290
Then I discovered that the children could and wanted to help.

31
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:41,250
I found dozens of ways to conserve time.

32
00:02:41,439 --> 00:02:47,570
Fewer trips to the store, less TV, less telephoning, less of those time killers.

33
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:50,929
This experience teaches us a lesson.

34
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,489
Capacity is a state of mind.

35
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:58,050
How much we can do depends on how much we think we can do.

36
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:04,209
When you really believe you can do more, your mind thinks creatively and shows you the way.

